<br>
Not in the name of my guild, but in my own name. I was the one who did the news section talking about the Kael incident.<br>
<br>
I was there and this is what I seen.<br>
<br>
1.- Hothgar came by us and told us he was pulling a big mob to the zone and that we should change our camp spot.<br>
2.- We asked him to wait 5 minutes to allow 1 of our porter to come back from a LD.<br>
3.- We aggroed a veteran.<br>
4.- We saw a Protector of Zek in our camp and Vindi crossing our path, less than 2 minutes after Hothgar warned us.<br>
<br>
My comments:<br>
1.- It was nice from Hothgar to tell us he was pulling. Though, I am sure there are other way to fight the Vindi without pulling him to the zone, especially when someone is in the Arena.<br>
2.- I realy hope, and I am quite sure it is true, that Hothgar didnt see those lines.<br>
3.- Our fault, we shouldnt have fight the vets, knowing you were pulling through us.<br>
4.- As we were fighting the Vet and 1 of our porter was LD, this was followed by 8 people being slaughtered and summoned.<br>
<br>
<br>
Anyway, I want to thank Magister to have help us to recover our corpse and for the warning from Hothgar.<br>
<br>
The news part was my own and shouldnt be credited to the entire guild. For this I apologise once again.<br>
<br>
I hope this will put an end to this misunderstanding.<br>
<br>
